pe="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>реки несли %sфарн%s</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the rivers carried %sfarn%s</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Sam."/><biblScope>74</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>farn fæcæwy!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>%sфарн%s шествует!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>%sfarn%s is marching!</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><bibl><ref target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>166</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>adæm farny zarǵytæ kodtoj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>народ пел (свадебные) песни %sфарна%s</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the people sang farn's wedding songs</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>127</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æncad ū, aǧ˳ysty farn ma rox kæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>тише, не забывай о %sфарне%s дома</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>hush, don't forget about the %sfarn%s at home</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>34</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*hvarnah-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>farr</w><gloss><q>блеск</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>великолепие</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>пышность</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*farn(frn, prn)</w><gloss><q>слава</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/><gloss><q>знамение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*farnbērtāk</w><gloss><q>носитель фарна</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>farnxwantak</w><gloss><q>наделенный фарном</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*dīni-farn</w><gloss><q>фарн религии</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (ср. ос. <xr><ref target="#entry_dīn"/></xr>%ii farn%i), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*βaγīfarn</w><gloss><q>божий фарн</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. ос. <xr><ref target="#entry_xucaw"/></xr>%ii farn%i) и др. (<bibl corresp=""><biblScope xml:lang="ru">I. Gerschevitch. Sogdian Compounds. Trans. Philol. Soc. 1945, стр. 139</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">I. Gerschevitch. Sogdian Compounds. Trans. Philol. Soc. 1945, p. 139</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>phārra(-farra)</w><gloss><q>звание</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/><gloss><q>достоинство</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl corresp="#ref_NTS"><biblScope>XV 15, 25, 114</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="xln"><lang/><w>φαρν</w></mentioned> (<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>258</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>φαρν-, farn-</w></mentioned> (<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>163–164, 195–196</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>farna-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>hvarənah-</w><gloss><q>слава</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>величие</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>сияние</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Обильно представлено в иранских собственных именах, в частности скифо-сарматских: <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>Φαρνης, Φαρνακης, Φαρναγος, Φαρνογος, Φαρνοξαρθος, Χοφαρνος, Σαιταφαρνης, ʽΟυαταφαρνης</w></mentioned> и др. В осетинском существует фамильное имя %iFærniatæ%i („Фарниевы“), а в нартовском эпосе один из главных героев зовется %iBuræ-færnyg%i | %iBoræ-færnug%i, т. е. „Бора наделенный фарном“. Cp. также <xr><ref target="#entry_Bonværnon"/></xr> (из %iBon-farnon%i) ‘планета Венера’, буквально „(вестница) дневного фарна“. Семантическая связь с ‘солнцем’ ясно выступает в охотничьем языке, где %ifærnæ%i д. значит ‘солнце’. Начальный %if%i из %ihv%i не характерен для восточноиранских языков, в частности для осетинского (должно было быть %ixw%i, %ix%i, как в <xr><ref target="#entry_xūr"/></xr> ‘солнце’, <xr><ref target="#entry_xor"/></xr> | %ixwar%i ‘хлеб в зерне’ и др.; ср., однако, <xr><ref target="#entry_fyn"/></xr> сон’ из %ihvafna-%i). Считают, что %ifarnah-%i мидийская форма, распространившаяся (через персидское посредство) по всему иранскому миру. (<bibl corresp="#ref_Gramm._sogd."><biblScope>I 134, II 154</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_BSL"><biblScope>XXXI %i2%i 72–76</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 86, III 81</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>40, 43, 71, 83, 163–164, 258</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*hvarnah-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>farr</w><gloss><q>shine</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>magnificence</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>splendour</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*farn(frn, prn)</w><gloss><q>fame</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/><gloss><q>sign</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*farnbērtāk</w><gloss><q>farn bearer</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>farnxwantak</w><gloss><q>provided with farn</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*dīni-farn</w><gloss><q>farn of the religion</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (cf. Ossetic <xr><ref target="#entry_dīn"/></xr>%ii farn%i), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*βaγīfarn</w><gloss><q>God's farn</q></gloss></mentioned> (cf. Ossetic <xr><ref target="#entry_xucaw"/></xr>%ii farn%i) etc. (<bibl corresp=""><biblScope xml:lang="ru">I. Gerschevitch. Sogdian Compounds. Trans. Philol. Soc. 1945, стр. 139</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Sogdian Compounds. Trans. Philol. Soc. 1945, p. 139</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>phārra(-farra)</w><gloss><q>rank</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/><gloss><q>dignity</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl corresp="#ref_NTS"><biblScope>XV 15, 25, 114</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="xln"><lang/><w>φαρν</w></mentioned> (<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>258</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>φαρν-, farn-</w></mentioned> (<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>163–164, 195–196</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>farna-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>hvarənah-</w><gloss><q>fame</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>greatness</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>shine</q></gloss></mentioned>, . It is abundantly represented in Iranian proper names, in particular in Scythian-Sarmatian: <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>Φαρνης, Φαρνακης, Φαρναγος, Φαρνογος, Φαρνοξαρθος, Χοφαρνος, Σαιταφαρνης, ʽΟυαταφαρνης</w></mentioned> etc. In Ossetic there is a family name %iFærniatæ%i (‘The Farnievs’), and in the Nart epos one of the main characters is called %iBuræ-færnyg%i | %iBoræ-færnug%i, i. e. ‘Bora who is provided with farn’. Cf. also <xr><ref target="#entry_Bonværnon"/></xr> (from %iBon-farnon%i) ‘Venus’, literally ‘(ambassadress) of the farn of the day’. The semantic relation to ‘sun’ is clearly seen in hunters' language, where Digor %ifærnæ%i means ‘sun’. The initial %if%i from %ihv%i is not typical of East Iranian languages, particularly, for Ossetic (there should have been %ixw%i, %ix%i, as in <xr><ref target="#entry_xūr"/></xr> ‘sun’, <xr><ref target="#entry_xor"/></xr> | %ixwar%i ‘grain bread’ etc.; however, cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_fyn"/></xr> ‘dream’ from %ihvafna-%i). It is considered that %ifarnah-%i is a Median form, which spread (via Persian) throughout the Iranian world. (<bibl corresp="#ref_Gramm._sogd."><biblScope>I 134, II 154</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_BSL"><biblScope>XXXI %i2%i 72–76</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 86, III 81</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>40, 43, 71, 83, 163–164, 258</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><note type="internal">мб ссылки/примеры в этимологии еще нужны? + очень сомнительный перевод всего</note></entry>